   "source": [
    "# DLBAIPNLP01 – Natural Language Processing (NLP)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Task 1: Sentiment Analysis on Movie Reviews\n",
    "\n",
    "This project builds and compares sentiment classification models using movie review datasets of increasing size and complexity.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "To simulate small-, medium-, and large-scale evaluations, the following datasets are used:\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Rotten Tomatoes Critic Reviews** (Kaggle) – 250,000+ reviews (sampled for small-scale testing)  \n",
    "> **Stanford Sentiment Treebank (SST)** – 11,855 labeled sentences (intermediate complexity)  \n",
    "> **IMDb Dataset** (Hugging Face) – 50,000 labeled reviews (large-scale validation)\n",
    "\n",
    "Models are first developed and tuned on smaller data, then tested on progressively larger datasets to evaluate generalization and robustness.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 1. Project Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "- Preprocess movie review text using NLP techniques (cleaning, lemmatization, stop word removal)\n",
    "- Apply three vectorization methods: CountVectorizer, TF-IDF, and word embeddings\n",
    "- Train and compare classifiers: Naive Bayes, SVM, Decision Trees, Random Forest, and Transformers\n",
    "- Evaluate models using Accuracy, F1-score, and Confusion Matrix\n",
    "- Validate model robustness by testing across all three datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## 2. Setup and Installation\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is developed in **JupyterLab** using a Python virtual environment.  \n",
    "The key libraries used include:\n",
    "\n",
    "- `pandas`, `nltk`, `spacy` – for text preprocessing  \n",
    "- `sklearn` – for vectorization and classical ML models  \n",
    "- `transformers`, `torch` – for fine-tuning DistilBERT  \n",
    "- `matplotlib`, `seaborn` – for visualization  \n",
    "- `datasets`, `kaggle` – for loading and downloading datasets  \n",
    "\n",
    "All packages are installed via `pip` or `conda` in a custom environment."
   ]
  },

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import spacy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load dataset\n",
    "df_rt = pd.read_csv(\"rotten_tomatoes_data/rotten_tomatoes_critic_reviews.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop missing and duplicate review content\n",
    "df_rt = df_rt.dropna(subset=[\"review_content\"]).drop_duplicates()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter only 'Fresh' and 'Rotten' labels, map to binary values\n",
    "df_rt = df_rt[df_rt['review_type'].isin(['Fresh', 'Rotten'])].copy()\n",
    "df_rt['label'] = df_rt['review_type'].map({'Fresh': 1, 'Rotten': 0})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Optional: sample 6,000 to speed up modeling while keeping class balance\n",
    "df_rt = df_rt.sample(n=6000, random_state=42).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load spaCy English model\n",
    "nlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define preprocessing: lowercase, remove stopwords, lemmatize, filter punctuation/numbers\n",
    "def preprocess_text(text):\n",
    "    doc = nlp(text.lower())\n",
    "    return \" \".join([token.lemma_ for token in doc if token.is_alpha and not token.is_stop])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply text cleaning\n",
    "df_rt['clean_text'] = df_rt['review_content'].apply(preprocess_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Final checks\n",
    "print(\"Cleaned dataset shape:\", df_rt.shape)\n",
    "print(\"\\nClass distribution:\\n\", df_rt['label'].value_counts())\n",
    "df_rt[['review_content', 'clean_text', 'label']].head()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# TF-IDF and embedding vectorization of cleaned review text\n",
    "# TF-IDF captures weighted term frequencies; embeddings encode semantic meaning\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
    "import spacy\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# TF-IDF Vectorization (top 5000 tokens)\n",
    "tfidf_vect_rt = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=5000)\n",
    "X_rt_tfidf = tfidf_vect_rt.fit_transform(df_rt['clean_text'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"TF-IDF feature matrix shape:\", X_rt_tfidf.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load spaCy medium English model with word vectors\n",
    "nlp_md = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_md\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Compute mean word embedding per document\n",
    "def get_mean_vector(doc):\n",
    "    tokens = [token.vector for token in nlp_md(doc) if token.has_vector]\n",
    "    return np.mean(tokens, axis=0) if tokens else np.zeros(nlp_md.vocab.vectors_length)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_rt_embed = np.vstack(df_rt['clean_text'].apply(get_mean_vector))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Embedding vector matrix shape:\", X_rt_embed.shape)"
   ]
  },

    "# Evaluate classical models on TF-IDF features (Rotten Tomatoes)\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train-test split (80/20 stratified)\n",
    "X_train_rt, X_test_rt, y_train_rt, y_test_rt = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X_rt_tfidf, df_rt['label'], test_size=0.2, stratify=df_rt['label'], random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluation function\n",
    "def evaluate_model(model, name, cmap_color):\n",
    "    model.fit(X_train_rt, y_train_rt)\n",
    "    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_rt)\n",
    "\n",
    "    acc = accuracy_score(y_test_rt, y_pred)\n",
    "    f1 = f1_score(y_test_rt, y_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"{name} Accuracy:\", round(acc, 4))\n",
    "    print(f\"{name} F1 Score:\", round(f1, 4))\n",
    "    print(\"\\nClassification Report:\\n\", classification_report(y_test_rt, y_pred))\n",
    "\n",
    "    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test_rt, y_pred)\n",
    "    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=cmap_color,\n",
    "                xticklabels=[\"Rotten\", \"Fresh\"], yticklabels=[\"Rotten\", \"Fresh\"])\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"{name} – TF-IDF (Rotten Tomatoes)\")\n",

    "# DistilBERT sentiment evaluation on Rotten Tomatoes\n",
    "from transformers import pipeline\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load DistilBERT sentiment pipeline\n",
    "classifier = pipeline(\"sentiment-analysis\", model=\"distilbert-base-uncased-finetuned-sst-2-english\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split Rotten Tomatoes into 80/20 (same split used for classical models)\n",
    "_, df_rt_test = train_test_split(df_rt, test_size=0.2, stratify=df_rt['label'], random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Predict on review_content using Hugging Face pipeline\n",
    "texts = df_rt_test['review_content'].tolist()\n",
    "predictions = classifier(texts)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert model output to 0/1 labels\n",
    "y_pred_bert = [1 if p['label'] == 'POSITIVE' else 0 for p in predictions]\n",
    "y_true_bert = df_rt_test['label'].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluate\n",
    "acc_bert = accuracy_score(y_true_bert, y_pred_bert)\n",
    "f1_bert = f1_score(y_true_bert, y_pred_bert)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"DistilBERT Accuracy:\", round(acc_bert, 4))\n",

    "# Confusion matrix\n",
    "cm = confusion_matrix(y_true_bert, y_pred_bert)\n",

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import spacy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the English language model\n",
    "nlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert HF dataset splits to DataFrames\n",
    "df_sst_train = pd.DataFrame(sst2['train'])\n",
    "df_sst_test = pd.DataFrame(sst2['validation'])  # Use validation as test set\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop nulls and duplicates\n",
    "df_sst_train = df_sst_train.dropna().drop_duplicates()\n",
    "df_sst_test = df_sst_test.dropna().drop_duplicates()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Function to clean and lemmatize text\n",
    "def preprocess_text(text):\n",
    "    doc = nlp(text.lower())\n",
    "    return \" \".join([token.lemma_ for token in doc if token.is_alpha and not token.is_stop])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply preprocessing\n",
    "df_sst_train['clean_text'] = df_sst_train['sentence'].apply(preprocess_text)\n",
    "df_sst_test['clean_text'] = df_sst_test['sentence'].apply(preprocess_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show dataset info\n",
    "print(\"Train shape:\", df_sst_train.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Test shape:\", df_sst_test.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nNull values in train:\")\n",
    "print(df_sst_train.isnull().sum())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nDuplicate rows in train:\", df_sst_train.duplicated().sum())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nLabel distribution in train:\")\n",
    "print(df_sst_train['label'].value_counts())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Preview cleaned data\n",
    "df_sst_train[['sentence', 'clean_text', 'label']].head()"
   ]
  },

    "from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Naive Bayes\n",
    "nb_model_sst = MultinomialNB()\n",
    "nb_model_sst.fit(X_train_sst, y_train_sst)\n",
    "y_pred_nb = nb_model_sst.predict(X_test_sst)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Naive Bayes Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_test_sst, y_pred_nb))\n",
    "print(\"F1 Score:\", f1_score(y_test_sst, y_pred_nb))\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test_sst, y_pred_nb))\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test_sst, y_pred_nb), annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=\"Blues\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Naive Bayes – SST-2\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# SVM\n",
    "svm_model_sst = LinearSVC()\n",
    "svm_model_sst.fit(X_train_sst, y_train_sst)\n",
    "y_pred_svm = svm_model_sst.predict(X_test_sst)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"SVM Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_test_sst, y_pred_svm))\n",
    "print(\"F1 Score:\", f1_score(y_test_sst, y_pred_svm))\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test_sst, y_pred_svm))\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test_sst, y_pred_svm), annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=\"Purples\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"SVM – SST-2\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Logistic Regression\n",
    "logreg_model_sst = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)\n",
    "logreg_model_sst.fit(X_train_sst, y_train_sst)\n",
    "y_pred_logreg = logreg_model_sst.predict(X_test_sst)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Logistic Regression Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_test_sst, y_pred_logreg))\n",
    "print(\"F1 Score:\", f1_score(y_test_sst, y_pred_logreg))\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test_sst, y_pred_logreg))\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.heatmap(confusion_matrix(y_test_sst, y_pred_logreg), annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=\"Greens\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Logistic Regression – SST-2\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# DistilBERT\n",
    "from transformers import pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load sentiment analysis pipeline with pre-trained DistilBERT\n",
    "classifier = pipeline(\"sentiment-analysis\", model=\"distilbert-base-uncased-finetuned-sst-2-english\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Use the raw sentences from the SST-2 test set\n",
    "texts = df_sst_test['sentence'].tolist()\n",
    "true_labels = df_sst_test['label'].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Predict using the classifier\n",
    "predictions = classifier(texts)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert Hugging Face labels to 0/1\n",
    "y_pred_bert = [1 if p['label'] == 'POSITIVE' else 0 for p in predictions]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluate\n",
    "print(\"DistilBERT Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(true_labels, y_pred_bert))\n",
    "print(\"DistilBERT F1 Score:\", f1_score(true_labels, y_pred_bert))\n",
    "print(\"\\nClassification Report:\\n\", classification_report(true_labels, y_pred_bert))\n",
    "\n",
    "cm = confusion_matrix(true_labels, y_pred_bert)\n",
    "sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=\"YlGnBu\", xticklabels=[\"Negative\", \"Positive\"], yticklabels=[\"Negative\", \"Positive\"])\n",
    "plt.title(\"DistilBERT – SST-2\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import spacy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load spaCy model once\n",
    "nlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define base path to extracted IMDb dataset\n",
    "base_path = \"data/aclImdb/aclImdb\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load reviews from folders and assign sentiment labels\n",
    "def load_reviews(folder_path, label):\n",
    "    return [\n",
    "        (open(os.path.join(folder_path, filename), encoding=\"utf-8\").read(), label)\n",
    "        for filename in os.listdir(folder_path)\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load and combine all reviews (train and test)\n",
    "train_pos = load_reviews(os.path.join(base_path, \"train\", \"pos\"), 1)\n",
    "train_neg = load_reviews(os.path.join(base_path, \"train\", \"neg\"), 0)\n",
    "test_pos = load_reviews(os.path.join(base_path, \"test\", \"pos\"), 1)\n",
    "test_neg = load_reviews(os.path.join(base_path, \"test\", \"neg\"), 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_imdb = pd.DataFrame(train_pos + train_neg + test_pos + test_neg, columns=[\"review\", \"label\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop duplicates and nulls\n",
    "df_imdb = df_imdb.dropna().drop_duplicates()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clean and lemmatize review text\n",
    "def preprocess_text(text):\n",
    "    doc = nlp(text.lower())\n",
    "    return \" \".join([token.lemma_ for token in doc if token.is_alpha and not token.is_stop])\n",
    "\n",
    "df_imdb['clean_text'] = df_imdb['review'].apply(preprocess_text)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dataset summary\n",
    "print(\"IMDb dataset shape:\", df_imdb.shape)\n",
    "print(\"\\nNull values:\\n\", df_imdb.isnull().sum())\n",
    "print(\"\\nDuplicate rows:\", df_imdb.duplicated().sum())\n",
    "print(\"\\nLabel distribution:\\n\", df_imdb['label'].value_counts())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Preview cleaned data\n",
    "df_imdb[['review', 'clean_text', 'label']].head()"
   ]
  },

    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vectorize the cleaned text\n",
    "tfidf_vect_imdb = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=5000)\n",
    "X = tfidf_vect_imdb.fit_transform(df_imdb['clean_text'])\n",
    "y = df_imdb['label'].values\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split data (80% train, 20% test)\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Function to train & evaluate models\n",
    "def evaluate_model(model, model_name, color):\n",
    "    model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"{model_name} Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred))\n",
    "    print(f\"F1 Score:\", f1_score(y_test, y_pred))\n",
    "    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))\n",
    "\n",
    "    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=color, xticklabels=[\"Negative\", \"Positive\"], yticklabels=[\"Negative\", \"Positive\"])\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"{model_name} – IMDb\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run evaluations\n",
    "evaluate_model(MultinomialNB(), \"Naive Bayes\", \"Blues\")\n",
    "evaluate_model(LinearSVC(), \"SVM\", \"Purples\")\n",
    "evaluate_model(LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000), \"Logistic Regression\", \"Greens\")"
   ]
  },

    "# Load DistilBERT with truncation/padding for long IMDb reviews (max 512 tokens)\n",
    "# - Prevents runtime errors when passing full-length text to the model\n",
    "from transformers import pipeline, AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForSequenceClassification\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load DistilBERT with truncation and padding enabled\n",
    "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"distilbert-base-uncased-finetuned-sst-2-english\")\n",
    "model = AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(\"distilbert-base-uncased-finetuned-sst-2-english\")\n",
    "\n",
    "classifier = pipeline(\n",
    "    \"sentiment-analysis\",\n",
    "    model=model,\n",
    "    tokenizer=tokenizer,\n",
    "    truncation=True,\n",
    "    padding=True\n",
    ")"
   ]

    "import torch\n",
    "\n",
    "# Limit to 5,000 reviews for faster DistilBERT evaluation\n",
    "texts = df_imdb_subset['review'].tolist()[:5000]\n",
    "labels = df_imdb_subset['label'].tolist()[:5000]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Storage for results\n",
    "y_pred_bert = []\n",
    "y_true_bert = []\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set model to evaluation mode\n",
    "model.eval()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Batch size\n",
    "batch_size = 16\n",
    "\n",
    "# Predict in batches\n",
    "for i in range(0, len(texts), batch_size):\n",
    "    batch_texts = texts[i:i+batch_size]\n",
    "    batch_labels = labels[i:i+batch_size]\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Encode with padding and truncation\n",
    "    inputs = tokenizer(batch_texts, truncation=True, padding=True, max_length=512, return_tensors=\"pt\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "        outputs = model(**inputs)\n",
    "        probs = torch.softmax(outputs.logits, dim=1)\n",
    "        preds = torch.argmax(probs, dim=1).tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "    y_pred_bert.extend(preds)\n",
    "    y_true_bert.extend(batch_labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Optional: progress update\n",
    "    if i % 512 == 0:\n",
    "        print(f\"Processed {i} / {len(texts)}\")"
   ]

    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.svm import LinearSVC\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vectorize IMDb clean_text using TF-IDF (5,000 features)\n",
    "tfidf_vect_imdb = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=5000)\n",
    "X = tfidf_vect_imdb.fit_transform(df_imdb['clean_text'])\n",
    "y = df_imdb['label'].values\n",
    "\n",
    "# Split into train/test (80/20 stratified)\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluation function\n",
    "def evaluate_model(model, model_name, cmap_color):\n",
    "    model.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "    acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "    f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f\"{model_name} Accuracy:\", round(acc, 4))\n",
    "    print(\"F1 Score:\", round(f1, 4))\n",
    "    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))\n",
    "\n",
    "    cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\n",
    "    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt=\"d\", cmap=cmap_color, \n",
    "                xticklabels=[\"Negative\", \"Positive\"], \n",
    "                yticklabels=[\"Negative\", \"Positive\"])\n",
    "    plt.title(f\"{model_name} – IMDb\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run models\n",
    "evaluate_model(MultinomialNB(), \"Naive Bayes\", \"Blues\")\n",
    "evaluate_model(LinearSVC(), \"SVM\", \"Purples\")\n",
    "evaluate_model(LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000), \"Logistic Regression\", \"Greens\")"
   ]
  },

    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
